member.value:
A bool. True if the BarTender 
window will be visible when it runs;
false if otherwise.

A bool. True if the BarTender 
window will be topmost when it runs;
false if otherwise.

value.para:
A bool. True specifies that a label format will be printed to file;
                false if otherwise. If set to true, the PrintToFileLicense must
                be set to a valid license key.

member.value:
A bool. True specifies
the use of a connected database when printing;
false if otherwise.

member.remarks:
This property is only guaranteed to be initialized
after the task has completed successfully;
otherwise an empty string will be returned.

member.summary:
Close the BarTender pool. This will stop all running bartend.exe processes. This function will not
return until all tasks are complete and BarTender processes have been stopped or when the timeout occurs,
whichever happens first.

member.value:
A bool. True if the BarTender 
window will be topmost when it runs;
false if otherwise.

A bool. A value of true if the printer 
will use its built-in serialization feature;
false if otherwise.

A bool.  A value of true if the printer is to store
all objects on the label format that do not vary per label;
false if otherwise.

member.remarks:
BarTender provides access to two LicenseConnections;
PrimaryConnection and
AlternateConnection. If BarTender attempts to connect using the PrimaryConnection and fails, it will then attempt to connect using the AlternateConnection.

member.value:
A bool. Returns true if the BarTender print engine process is running; 
false if
otherwise.
